com.rli.util.identityData

Class IdentityFilter

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.rli.util.identityData.IdentityFilter

  • public class IdentityFilter
extends java.lang.Object
    An IdentityFilter is a class that is used to represent filters that can be applied or matched against IdentityData attributes and their values. The filters in this class use the SCIM2 filter notation which can be found here: RFC-7644, section 3.4.2.2 (Filtering)

      • fromString

        public static IdentityFilter fromString(java.lang.String identityFilterStr)
                                 throws IdentityDataException
        Returns an instance of an IdentityFilter based on the specified String value. The specified String value should follow the SCIM2 filter format: RFC-7644, section 3.4.2.2 (Filtering)
        Parameters:
        identityFilterStr - The string representation of a filter (in the SCIM2 filter format).
        Returns:
        an instance of an IdentityFilter based on the specified String value
        Throws:
        IdentityDataException - If the specified String cannot be parsed or is invalid (not respecting the SCIM2 filter format).

        public static boolean applyCondition(IdentityData ce,

        Indicates if the attribute found in the IdentityData object matches the condition described by the given parameters.
        Parameters:
        ce - A IdentityData object containing a list of attributes and their values.
        attributeName - The name of the attribute on which the condition will be checked.
        comparisonValue - A value used for checking a condition, if the operator requires a comparison value.
        operator - The operator for the condition.
        comparisonType - The comparison type for the condition.
        Returns:
